**Section 5: Summary of Findings**

**5.1 Critical Path Items**

The following items are on the critical path for POC development and
should be prioritized in client discussions:

-   Actuarial factor tables for J&S payment options (Q-CALC-04)

-   Rounding methodology confirmation (Q-CALC-01)

-   Service credit calculation precision method (Q-CALC-02)

-   Early retirement reduction proration method (Q-CALC-03)

-   RMC currency confirmation (Q-ELIG-02)

-   Current technology landscape (Q-OPS-01)

**5.2 Document Cleanup Items**

These are internal corrections to make before client-facing
presentations:

-   Update BUILD_PLAN.md to correct 6% reference (Section 2.6)

-   Align Case 4 50% J&S factor with Decision 17 standard (Section 2.7)

-   Add note to doc05 that AMS values are illustrative (Section 2.8)

-   Model pop-up provision in payment option workspace (Section 2.2)

-   Distinguish two spousal consent forms in process definition (Section
    2.4)

**5.3 Areas of Strength**

The project knowledge base is remarkably comprehensive. Several areas
are particularly well-documented and internally consistent:

-   Tier determination logic (hire date boundaries, eligibility rules)
    --- consistent across all 14+ documents

-   Service purchase exclusion rules --- correctly modeled in every case
    file, doc, and test fixture

-   DRO calculation methodology and sequencing --- consistent and
    verified against DERP forms

-   Process definition stages --- align well with DERP's published
    five-step member process

-   CRITICAL-001 resolution process --- exemplary research methodology
    with multiple source verification
